Package org.apache.logging.log4j.spi

Class AbstractResourceLogger

java.lang.Object
org.apache.logging.log4j.spi.AbstractLogger
org.apache.logging.log4j.spi.ExtendedLoggerWrapper
org.apache.logging.log4j.spi.AbstractResourceLogger
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Logger, ExtendedLogger, LocationAwareLogger
Direct Known Subclasses:
ScopedResourceLogger
public abstract class AbstractResourceLogger extends ExtendedLoggerWrapper
Logger for resources. The Supplier provides resource attributes that should be included in all log events generated from the current resource. The Supplier may be called when the Logger is created or for every log event. Therefore, care should be taken to make the Supplier as efficient as possible to avoid performance issues. Unlike regular Loggers ResourceLoggers CANNOT be declared to be static. A ResourceLogger must be declared as a class member that will be garbage collected along with the instance of the resource.
